	<queries>
		<query>
			<formula>A&lt;&gt; !MinorRoad.Red imply MinorRoad.Red</formula>
			<comment>If minor-road's light isn't red, it will eventually become red.
</comment>
		</query>
		<query>
			<formula>A[] MinorRoad.Green and TrafficController.y &lt; 30 imply MainRoad.Red and (SensorMainRoad.High or !SensorMainRoad.High)</formula>
			<comment>If minor-road is green for less then 30 units of time then it will be green until then even regardeless traffic level on major-road.</comment>
		</query>
		<query>
			<formula>A[] SensorMainRoad.High and MainRoad.Green and (TrafficController.y &lt; 60 ) imply MinorRoad.Red and (SensorMinorRoad.High or !SensorMinorRoad.High)</formula>
			<comment>If there is high traffic in major-road and its green lights have been on, for less than 60 minutes, then it will remain green until then.</comment>
		</query>
		<query>
			<formula>A&lt;&gt; ((!SensorMinorRoad.Non_existence imply MinorRoad.Green) &amp; (!SensorMainRoad.Non_existence imply MainRoad.Green))</formula>
			<comment>If there are cars waiting they will eventually have green light.</comment>
		</query>
		<query>
			<formula>A[] MinorRoad.Green imply !MainRoad.Green</formula>
			<comment>The minor-road and the major-road ligths cannot be green at the same time.</comment>
		</query>
		<query>
			<formula>A[] not deadlock</formula>
			<comment>The system never enters in a deadlock state.</comment>
		</query>
		<query>
			<formula>E&lt;&gt; MainRoad.Red</formula>
			<comment>The major-road light can go red.</comment>
		</query>
		<query>
			<formula>E&lt;&gt; MinorRoad.Green</formula>
			<comment>Minor-road light can go green.</comment>
		</query>
		<query>
			<formula>MinorRoad.Yellow and (MinorRoad.x &gt; 5) --&gt; !MinorRoad.Yellow</formula>
			<comment>Yellow ligth on minor-road stays on for 5 units of time.</comment>
		</query>
		<query>
			<formula>MainRoad.Yellow and (MainRoad.x &gt; 5) --&gt; !MainRoad.Yellow</formula>
			<comment>Yellow ligth on major-road stays on for 5 units of time.</comment>
		</query>
